## LOOM ORCHESTRATION REFERENCE

**Session start:** 1) read knowledge files (Rule 12); 2) check `.work/signals/` for your session ID; 3) read your stage description — look for `EXECUTION PLAN` blocks; 4) spawn specified subagents per Rule 6; 5) signal found? execute; no signal? ask the user.

**Stage lifecycle:** `WaitingForDeps → Queued → Executing → Completed → Verified` (also `Blocked`, `NeedsHandoff`, `WaitingForInput`). Retry a failed merge with `loom stage merge <stage-id>`.

**Context thresholds:** default budget 65% (per-stage `context_budget` overrides), hard maximum 75%.

| Usage         | Action                       |
| ------------- | ---------------------------- |
| <60%          | Normal                       |
| 60% to budget | Warning shown                |
| At budget     | BudgetExceeded               |
| ≥75%          | Stop. Handoff (hard stop 4). |

**CLI:** `loom run` (start) | `loom status` (dashboard) | `loom stop` | `loom check <stage-id> [--suggest]` (goal-backward verification) | `loom map [--deep] [--focus <area>]` | `loom repair [--fix]`.

**Handoff template** (`.work/handoffs/YYYY-MM-DD-desc.md`):

```markdown
# Handoff: [Description]

**Stage**: [id] | **Context**: [X]%

## Completed

[file:line refs]

## Next Steps

[prioritized tasks]
```

**References:** cite code as `src/auth.ts:45-120`, not "the auth file".

